1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on the usability of a clinical system that provides operational support to doctors using mobile technologies for delivering care to patients. The use of vocal and touch interfaces is also investigated. This aligns with the scope of the HC sub-category.

2. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) - The paper mentions the negative impact of mobile technologies on patient-centeredness and the potential for medical errors. This highlights the importance of cybersecurity and privacy in healthcare systems, which falls under the scope of the CYBER sub-category.

3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper presents a clinical system that exploits concepts from Business Process Management to manage a specific class of care procedures and support their execution and mobile orchestration among doctors. This aligns with the scope of the SE sub-category.

4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents a system that aims to minimize medical errors in healthcare delivery. This falls under the scope of the CE sub-category, which focuses on the application of computational methods to solve problems in various domains.
